# Issue tracker

Work is tracked as **GitHub Issues** on this repository. Use the **`gh` CLI** from the repo root; the repo is inferred from `git remote`.

Also follow **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root for Next.js-specific agent rules.

**Essentials**

- Create: `gh issue create --title "…" --body "…"`
- Read (with discussion): `gh issue view <n> --comments`
- List / filter: `gh issue list` (add `--label`, `--state` as needed)
- Comment: `gh issue comment <n> --body "…"`
- Labels: `gh issue edit <n> --add-label "…"` / `--remove-label "…"`
- Close: `gh issue close <n> --comment "…"`

Full conventions: `docs/agents/issue-tracker.md`.
